# This directory is bind-mounted to /home/user inside the container — it is
# Haggai's persistent, isolated home. It starts empty; the container seeds his
# dotfiles, RustDesk config, and Codex config here on first run, and everything
# he creates afterwards persists here on the host. Do not delete this directory
# (it is the bind-mount target); use ./teardown.sh --purge to clear its contents.
